{
  "texts": [
    "See 'AI-Trainingset -Tag de Tekst voor Named Entity Recognition (NER)', INT Taalmaterialen, online: https://taalmaterialen.ivdnt.org/download/aitrainingset1-0/ [20-10-2022].",
    "Using the existing landscape of crowdsourcing projects as examples, we find roughly two different methods of acknowledging volunteers.",
    "First, some projects refer to their volunteers in general, as if they were a homogeneous group (see figures 7 and 8).",
    "Some do so for practical reasons, others to intentionally emphasise the collective effort instead of the individual.",
    "Second, there are projects, especially smaller ones, that acknowledge their volunteers by listing them with their full credentials in recognition of their work (see figures 9 and 10)."
  ]
}